org.snrg_nyc.model

Interface UI_Interface

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BusinessLogic

    public interface UI_Interface
    The public-facing business logic for use by the user interface of an SNRG frontend. This interface and any implementations of it should be the only public classes in this package.
    Version:
    0.2
    Author:
    Devin Hastings

      • scratch_addConditionalDistribution

        int scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> dependencyConditions,
                                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> probabilities)
                                throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Add a conditional Distribution to the current scratch property
        Parameters:
        dependencyConditions - A map of integer IDs, which must be one of the IDs from scratch_getDependencies()(); and a label that the dependency must be, which is one of the labels in the node property. All pIDs are optional, but there must be exactly one label per pID.
        probabilities - A map of all the range labels in the scratch property to floating point values representing the probability of that range in the distribution. Each label must appear exactly once in the map. (these probabilities are relative, and there is no special requirements for them). Each label must be in the map exactly once.
        Returns:
        The ID of the new conditional Distribution
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the dependencyConditions or probabilities aren't valid , or if the scratch property is currently null, which means scratch_new(String, String, String) needs to be called.

      • scratch_updateConditionalDistribution

        void scratch_updateConditionalDistribution(int cid,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> dependencyConditions,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> probabilities)
                                    throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Replace the attributes of a conditional distribution with new information.

        See scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String>, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Float>) for the requirements of dependencyConditions and probabilities.

        Parameters:
        cid - The ID of the conditional distribution, as received from scratch_addConditionalDistribution(Map, Map) or scratch_getConditionalDistributionIDs()
        dependencyConditions - See scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String>, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Float>) for requirements
        probabilities - See scratch_addConditionalDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer, java.lang.String>, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.Float>) for requirements
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the ID does not point to a distribution, or the requirements for the parameters are not met , or if the scratch property is currently null, which means scratch_new(String, String, String) needs to be called.

      • scratch_reorderConditionalDistributions

                                      throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Set the order in which the conditional distributions are to be checked.
        Parameters:
        ordering - A list of IDs of the conditional distributions in the order they are to be checked
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if any of the IDs in the list do not point to a conditional distribution in the scratch object , or if the scratch property is currently null, which means scratch_new(String, String, String) needs to be called.

      • scratch_setDefaultDistribution

        void scratch_setDefaultDistribution(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> distribution)
                             throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Set the default distribution of the scratch property.
        Parameters:
        distribution - A map of all the range labels in the scratch property to floating point values representing the probability of that range in the distribution. Each label must appear exactly once in the map.
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - Thrown if the requirements for the distribution are not met , or if the scratch property is currently null, which means scratch_new(String, String, String) needs to be called.

      • scratch_commitToNodeProperties

        int scratch_commitToNodeProperties()
                            throws UI_Interface.UIException
        Finalize the scratch property and add it to the structure of node properties. In its current state, this clears the scratch property automatically, and there is no way to edit or remove an added node property, so it is important to make sure the property is how the user wants it before committing.
        Returns:
        The node property ID of the new property, which is also available through nodeProp_getPropertyIDs()
        Throws:
        UI_Interface.UIException - There are several reasons that this exception may be thrown, here is a list of examples:
        • The scratch property is null, which means scratch_new(String, String, String) was never called
        • The scratch property has the same name as another node property
        • The scratch property does not have a default distribution, but needs one.
        And various other messages. Throwable.getMessage() should yield more information.
